  "title": "HR Administrator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Descriptions</strong></p><ul><li>Support in daily operational and administrative duties</li><li>Process HR related purchase order and invoices and obtain necessary approval for payment</li><li>Compile all necessary documents to create new hire’s p/file and update HR system</li><li>Create staff pass for new hire or replacement pass for existing staff</li><li>Preparation of HR letters such as bond agreement, certificate of employment, confirmation letter as required</li><li>Assist in coordinating and organising HR related events, staff engagement activities and training programmes</li><li>Perform any other duties or projects as assigned by the supervisor</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>O/A Levels or Diploma or equivalent with at least 2 years of experience</li><li>Meticulous, resourceful, has initiative and ability to work independently</li><li>Ability to multi-task and work in a fast pace environment to meet tight deadlines</li><li>Competent in MS Office, especially Excel and PowerPoint</li></ul>",
